snippet.textDisplay:
I myself am disabled, I would love to have a vehicle for disabled people. It would be even nicer to have it donated because I am on a fixed budget and broke as hell but I know that won't happen.

I know I'm not the only person in that situation. So I would love to see somebody who truly deserving of it, receive it.

I do watch a lot of car Channels, most of them are getting very commercial almost like they are getting a lot less "Creator made" and a lot more "professionally made" almost like they are done with professional actors in a television Studio. It is detracting more and more from what the appeal that YouTube once was. If I want to see stuff on TV, I will cancel my internet connection and get cable TV instead. But that's not what viewers like me want to see.

I'm just one voice of hundreds of thousands of watchers, so my opinion doesn't mean much.
